! Focus model

The palette is one popup with up to seven focusable sections, partitioned into two groups:

* ''pills group'' (top of the palette, visually stacked): ''preset'' (only when ≥ 1 preset exists), ''visibility'' (only when ≥ 1 visibility rule active), ''filter'' (only when ≥ 1 filter active), ''view'' (only when ≥ 2 views declared)
* ''main group'': ''input'' (search box), ''menu'' (result list), ''details'' (preview drawer, only when open)

The active section gets the browser-level focus and a visual cue; keyboard gestures route accordingly. ''Tab'' cycles within the current group; ''Shift-Tab'' jumps between groups (lands on the bottom-most pill when entering pills, on input when returning). ''↑ / ↓'' inside the pill group walks vertically across rows — ↑ from input enters pills at the bottom-most row, ↓ from the bottom-most pill drops back into input. Esc steps "outward" — section → input → close.

! Hotkey

|!Key |!Section |!Action |
|''Ctrl-Space'' |any |Open the palette |
|''Tab'' |any |Cycle focus within the current group only: pills (preset → visibility → filter → view) or main (input → menu → details). Rows only join the cycle when active. |
|''Shift-Tab'' |any |Jump between the two groups. From main → bottom-most active pill; from pills → input. |
|''Enter'' |input / menu / details |Fire the selected item and close the palette. ''Exception:'' in input focus, if the current text matches a known filter or visibility prefix with a non-empty argument, Enter commits that pill instead. |
|''Ctrl-Enter'' |any |Fire the selected item but keep the palette open. Shift-Enter is a silent alias for back-compat (removed in v0.3). |
|''Ctrl-DEL / Ctrl-Backspace'' |any |Clear ''both'' constraint strips (filters + visibility) AND the active-preset marker in one step. |
|''Esc'' |input |Close the palette entirely (no stage-pop intermediate) |
|''↓'' |input |Step into the menu (only if results exist) |
|''↑'' |input |Enter the pill group at the bottom-most active pill row (no-op if no pills active) |
|''(typing)'' |input |Filter the current stage. When the text matches a filter prefix, the input picks up a blue underline ("↵ commit filter: …"); when it matches a visibility prefix, an orange underline ("↵ commit visibility: …"); when it matches a leader key, an amber underline — leader fires after 200ms idle, any keystroke cancels. |
|''Esc'' |any (in pick-mode) |Cancel pick-mode — return to prior view without committing a filter |
|''Esc'' |preset / visibility / filter / view / menu / details |Return focus to the input (without closing) |
|''← / →'' |preset / visibility / filter / view |Move focus between pills within the row (clamps at edges) |
|''↑ / ↓'' |preset / visibility / filter / view |Walk between pill rows. ↓ at the bottom-most row drops into input; ↑ at the top-most row no-ops. |
|''Enter / Space'' |view |Activate the highlighted view — pops the stack to root, rebuilds the menu |
|''Enter / Space'' |preset |Apply the focused preset (replaces filters + visibility, switches view, keeps palette open). The applied preset becomes the ''active'' preset until cleared. |
|''Ctrl-Enter'' |preset |Overwrite the focused preset with the current state. Only effective when the focused pill IS the active preset AND it's dirty (current state diverges from the captured baseline). |
|''DEL / Backspace'' |preset |Push a confirm-drill to permanently delete the focused preset tiddler. Confirm with Enter, cancel with Esc. |
|''Home / End'' |preset |Jump focus to the first / last preset |
|''DEL / Backspace'' |filter / visibility |Remove the focused pill |
|''Enter'' |filter / visibility |Move focus into the details pane to scroll through the full help text |
|''↑'' |menu |Move selection up; at top-of-list, returns focus to input |
|''↓'' |menu |Move selection down |
|''→'' |menu |Drill into the selected item (push a new stage) |
|''←'' |menu |Pop one stage (back). No-op at the root stage — closing the palette is reserved for Esc. |
|''Space'' on toggle |menu |Flip the bound value (palette stays open) |
|''Space'' on text/number |menu |Enter edit mode — bound value pushed into input, Enter commits, Esc cancels |
|''+ / -'' on number |menu |Adjust by `ca-step` (default 1). Shift = `ca-step-medium` (5). Ctrl = `ca-step-large` (20). Matched on physical key (Equal/NumpadAdd/Minus/NumpadSubtract) so layout is irrelevant. |
|''DEL / Backspace'' |menu |On an overridden setting → confirm drill to restore default. On a non-shadow tiddler in a diagnostic list → confirm drill to delete. Otherwise no-op. |
|''Shift-DEL / Shift-Backspace'' |menu (root stage) |Add a ''hide-entry'' visibility pill for the selected row — the entry disappears from the root menu until the pill is removed. |
|''← / →'' |details |Switch template tab when multiple templates apply |
|''↑ / ↓'' |details |Scroll the drawer natively |
|''Hold Ctrl'' |any |Open the details drawer; release to hide. Always-on mode keeps it visible. Suppressed in edit mode. |
|''Click'' on a result row |menu |Sets focus → selects → fires (Shift-click = keep open) |
|''Click'' on a filter / visibility pill |filter / visibility |Focus that pill (the × on the pill removes it) |
|''Click'' on a view pill |view |Activate that view |
|''Click'' on a preset pill |preset |Apply that preset |
|''Click'' on a breadcrumb segment | |Pop back to that stage |
|''Hover'' on any row | |Native browser tooltip shows the row's `ca-hint` text. |
|''Hover'' on a pill |filter / visibility / preset |Native browser tooltip shows the pill's hint. |

The hotkey is configured at `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open`.

! Tags

|!Tag |!Purpose |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry` |Root-stage menu item |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action` |Per-entity-type action menu item |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/setting` |Setting toggle exposed under the engine's "Settings" entry |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/diagnostic` |Diagnostic item exposed under the engine's "Diagnostics" entry |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/configuration` |Aggregated under the engine's "Configuration" root entry (Settings, Diagnostics, etc.) |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/template` |Detail-pane template — wikitext rendered with `currentTiddler` bound to the picked item |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/filter` |Declarative ''filter'' — adds a removable pill whose expression is appended (intersected) to every result-list filter |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/visibility` |Declarative ''visibility rule'' — adds a removable pill whose predicate filter hides matching root entries |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/view` |Declarative view — strategy for building the root menu (flat or tree). Each view appears as a pill in the view strip |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/leader` |Leader-key gesture — key + idle window fires a wikitext action chain |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/preset` |Saved `(view, filters, visibility)` bundle — surfaced as a pill in the preset strip |

! Fields

|!Field |!Type |!Where |!Purpose |
|`ca-name` |string |entry, action |Display name in the row |
|`ca-hint` |string |entry, action |Subtitle / right-aligned hint |
|`ca-icon` |string |entry, action |Single character or emoji prefix |
|`ca-order` |number |entry, action |Sort key (lower = higher in list, default 100) |
|`ca-kind` |`leaf`\|`drill`\|`toggle`\|`number`\|`text`\|`date` |entry, action, setting |Leaf fires actions, drill pushes next stage, toggle flips a bound boolean, number adjusts via `+/-` (Space to type-set), text edits a string via Space → type → Enter, date adjusts via `+/-` ±day (Shift ±month, Ctrl ±year), Space → typed-edit with smart parser |
|`ca-actions` |wikitext |leaf items |Fired on Enter |
|`ca-confirm` |`yes`\|empty |leaf items |When `yes`, the leaf's actions are wrapped in a confirm-drill stage rather than fired directly. The consequence text shows the cost of confirming (e.g. "Delete tiddler X"). |
|`ca-confirm-consequence` |string |leaf with `ca-confirm:yes` |Text shown in the details drawer of the confirm stage. Supports `<<picked>>` / `<<parent-picked>>` / `<<stage-N-picked>>` substitution. |
|`ca-after-fire` |`close`\|`pop` |leaf |Post-fire behaviour. Default `close` (closes the palette). `pop` fires the action then pops one stage, keeping the palette open — for single-select sub-drills inside a field-edit flow, so the user lands back on the field stage with their pick already applied. |
|`ca-entity-type` |string\|`*` |action |Entity type this action applies to, or `*` for global |
|`ca-default` |`yes`\|empty |action |Marks the "Enter on entity result" default action |
|`ca-next-scope` |filter |drill items |Filter expression for the new stage's items (mutually exclusive with `ca-items-from`) |
|`ca-items-from` |filter |drill items |Filter that returns one JSON-encoded item shape per result. The palette parses each as a synthetic cascade item (no backing tiddler). Use for stages populated from configuration data rather than tiddlers. Mutually exclusive with `ca-next-scope`. |
|`ca-next-title` |string |drill items |Title shown in breadcrumb for the new stage |
|`ca-next-entity-type` |string |drill items |Sets the next stage's entity type (enables action-menu drilling on Tab) |
|`ca-next-default-action` |wikitext |drill items |Fired on Enter in the next stage when no entity default exists |
|`ca-next-as-link` |`yes`\|empty |drill items |When `yes`, the next-stage filter results render as plain link rows (no chevron, Enter navigates) even if the result tiddlers carry `ca-kind`. Use for inspector / diagnostic lists. |
|`ca-group` |string |entry, action |Override the visual cluster label. Defaults to the contributing plugin's `name`. Headers are suppressed when only one cluster is present in a stage. |
|`ca-visibility-filter` |filter |entry |If present and returns no results, the entry is hidden from the root menu |
|`ca-bind-tiddler` |string |toggle, number, text, date, drill |Target tiddler holding the bound value. On a `drill` (e.g. a single/multi-select picker sub-drill) this is purely informational — the palette renders the current bound value on the right of the row so the user sees their pick. |
|`ca-bind-field` |string |toggle, number, text, date, drill |Target field (default `text`). Same dual role as `ca-bind-tiddler` on drills. |
|`ca-bind-path` |string |toggle, number, text, date |Optional comma-separated walk inside the JSON-decoded field text (e.g. `prefs,layout`). Omit to bind the whole field. |
|`ca-bind-type` |scribetype name |toggle, number, text, date |Scribetype handler used for value round-trip (default `text/plain`). `application/x-string-array` enables list-membership semantics on toggle. `application/x-tw-date` / `application/x-tw-datetime` round-trip date kinds (the latter is the default for date kinds when unset). Requires `rimir/scribe`. |
|`ca-true-value` |string |toggle |Value written for "on" state (default `yes`). For `string-array` binds, this is the list element added/removed by the toggle. |
|`ca-false-value` |string |toggle |Value written for "off" state (default `no`). Ignored for string-array binds (the toggle removes `ca-true-value` from the list instead). |
|`ca-min` |number |number |Lower clamp. Together with `ca-max` triggers the inline slider render. |
|`ca-max` |number |number |Upper clamp. |
|`ca-step` |number |number |Step for bare `+/-` (default 1) |
|`ca-step-medium` |number |number |Step for Shift-`+/-` (default 5) |
|`ca-step-large` |number |number |Step for Ctrl-`+/-` (default 20) |
|`ca-step-day` / `-month` / `-year` |number |date |Step for bare/Shift/Ctrl `+/-` respectively on a date row (each defaults to 1) |
|`ca-date-format` |TW format-date string |date |Display format for the row value. Default `DD.MM.YYYY`. Examples: `YYYY-0MM-0DD` (ISO), `DDth MMM YYYY` (long). |
|`ca-default-value` |number |number |Value used when the bound field is empty / unparseable |
|`ca-help` |string (multiline) |entry, action, setting |Longer-form help text shown in the details drawer. Falls back to `ca-hint` when absent. |
|`ca-template-applies` |filter |template |Evaluated with `currentTiddler` bound to the picked item; template applies if filter returns the picked title. Omit for a universal template. |
|`ca-template-name` |string |template |Display name on the template tab (when multiple templates apply). |
|`ca-filter-name` |string |filter |Display name. Required. |
|`ca-filter-prefix` |string |filter |Input-prefix that triggers the filter (e.g. `/`, `prefix:`). Optional. Matched greedy-by-length, across both filter and visibility tag families. |
|`ca-filter-arg` |`text`\|`tag`\|`tiddler`\|`none` |filter |How the trailing input is interpreted. Default `text`. |
|`ca-filter-expr` |filter snippet |filter |Appended (intersected) with every result-list filter. Use `<arg>` as the argument operand placeholder; engine substitutes `[<arg>]` at pill-push time. |
|`ca-filter-chip` |string template |filter |Plain-text pill label. Use `<<arg>>` for substitution. Defaults to `ca-filter-name`. |
|`ca-filter-hint` / `-help` |string |filter |Hover / details-pane help. |
|`ca-visibility-name` |string |visibility |Display name. Required. |
|`ca-visibility-prefix` |string |visibility |Input-prefix (e.g. `hide:`). Optional. |
|`ca-visibility-arg` |`text`\|`tag`\|`tiddler`\|`none` |visibility |How the trailing input is interpreted. Default `text`. |
|`ca-visibility-expr` |filter snippet |visibility |Predicate evaluated per root entry with `<currentTiddler>` bound to its title — non-empty result hides the entry. Use `<arg>` for the operand placeholder. |
|`ca-visibility-chip` / `-hint` / `-help` |string |visibility |Same shape as the filter equivalents. |
|`ca-view-name` |string |view |Display name on the view-strip pill and as the root breadcrumb segment |
|`ca-view-hint` |string |view |Tooltip on hover; appears in the details pane when the view pill is focused |
|`ca-view-default` |`yes`\|empty |view |One view declares `yes` to be the initial selection on page load |
|`ca-view-source` |filter |view |TW filter producing the source-tiddler set |
|`ca-view-tree-strategy` |`path-segments`\|`parent-tag`\|`custom-key`\|empty |view |Empty = flat view. Tree strategies fold sources into a hierarchy that the user drills into |
|`ca-view-tree-key` |filter |view (custom-key) |Per-source filter returning a list of path segments |
|`ca-view-root-tag` |string |view (parent-tag) |Stop-tag for the ancestor walk |
|`ca-view-sort` |`alphabetical`\|`natural`\|`by-field`\|`custom` |view |Row sort policy; default `alphabetical` |
|`ca-view-sort-field` |string |view (by-field) |Field name read off each row |
|`ca-view-sort-key` |filter |view (custom) |Per-row filter returning a sortable key |
|`ca-view-containers-first` |`yes`\|`no` |view |Containers float above leaves at each tree level. Default `yes` for tree views |
|`ca-view-show-count` |`yes`\|`no` |view |Render a child-count badge on tree-container rows. Default `no` |
|`ca-view-count-format` |template |view |Badge template, default ` (<<count>>)` |
|`ca-view-row-name` / `-hint` / `-icon` / `-kind` / `-group` / `-order` / `-next-scope` / `-items-from` |filter |view |Per-source overrides; evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the source. Unset filters fall through to the source's own `ca-*` field |
|`ca-view-row-actions` |filter ''or'' wikitext |view |Action fired on a leaf pick. If parses as a filter returning a result, the result is the action wikitext (fetch source's `ca-actions`); otherwise the raw value is the wikitext template with `<<currentTiddler>>` substituted at fire time |
|`ca-position` |string |entry |Position fallback used by every view when no per-view override is set. `at-root` (default), `none`, a tree path like `Tools/Search`, or multi-position via `:` / newlines |
|`ca-position-<view-slug>` |string |entry |Per-view position override. Slug is the view tiddler's basename. Same value space as `ca-position` |
|`ca-view-pick-mode` |`yes`\|empty |view |When `yes`, Enter on any row commits the row's effective path as a filter arg and returns to the prior view. Right-arrow still drills. |
|`ca-view-pick-emits-filter` |filter-title |view (pick-mode) |Filter tiddler whose `ca-filter-expr` receives the picked path as `<arg>` |
|`ca-leader-key` |string |leader |Trigger string (single char or short multi-char). Required. |
|`ca-leader-name` |string |leader |Display name (for catalogues / details rendering). |
|`ca-leader-hint` |string |leader |One-line hint shown in the footer during the idle window. |
|`ca-leader-help` |string (multiline) |leader |Help shown in the details pane during the idle window. Falls back to hint. |
|`ca-leader-idle-ms` |number |leader |Override the default 200ms idle window. |
|`ca-leader-actions` |wikitext |leader |Fired when the leader commits. Typically `<$action-sendmessage>` calls to one of the widget messages. Required. |
|`ca-preset-name` |string |preset |Display name (e.g. "PersonsOfA"). Required. |
|`ca-preset-view` |view-title |preset |View active at save time. |
|`ca-preset-constraints` |JSON |preset |Object `{"filters": [{title, arg}, …], "visibility": [{title, arg}, …]}` — both lists at save time. |

! Settings

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Effect |
|`$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open` |`ctrl+space` |Hotkey to open the palette |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/max-results` |`30` |Cap on items shown per stage |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/grouping-enabled` |`yes` |Cluster result rows by contributing plugin with section headers. Toggle live via Settings → Grouping. |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/soft-depth-warning` |`10` |Stage-stack depth that triggers a console warning. Adjust live via Settings → Soft depth warning. |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/details-always-on` |`no` |Keep the details drawer visible without holding Ctrl. Toggle live via Settings → Details always on. |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/popup-width` |`50` |Popup width in `vw` (clamped to [20, 95]). |

! JavaScript message

|!Message |!Dispatched from |!Handled by |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-open` |Keyboard shortcut binding or any wikitext via `$action-sendmessage` |The widget's listener on `$tw.rootWidget` |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-add-filter` |Leaders / external triggers |The widget; pushes the named filter (no-arg) or pre-fills the input with its prefix for `text`/`tag`/`tiddler` args. Parameter: `filter` = filter tiddler title. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-set-filter` |Leaders |Push the named filter with an explicit literal arg (no interactive prefill). Parameters: `filter`, `arg`. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-add-visibility` |Leaders / external triggers |Same shape as add-filter but pushes onto the visibility strip. Parameter: `visibility`. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-set-visibility` |Leaders |Same shape as set-filter but for visibility. Parameters: `visibility`, `arg`. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-reset-filters` |Leaders |Clear all filter pills. No parameters. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-reset-visibility` |Leaders |Clear all visibility pills. No parameters. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-reset-constraints` |Reset-constraints leader (`x`), Ctrl-DEL |Clear both constraint strips in one step. No parameters. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-set-view` |Leaders, view-pill clicks |Activate the named view. Parameter: `view`. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-apply-preset` |Preset-pill clicks, leaders |Replay a preset. Parameter: `preset`. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-save-preset` |`s` leader |Open the save mini-prompt. No parameters. |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-recall-preset` |`r` leader |Move focus to the preset pill strip. No parameters. |

! Filter substitution variables

|!Variable |!Available in |!Value |
|`<<query>>` |entries, actions, filters |Current input text |
|`<<picked>>` |action |Title of the item just picked |
|`<<parent-picked>>` |entries, actions, filters |Title picked in the parent stage |
|`<<stage-N-picked>>` |entries, actions, filters |Title picked at stage index N (root = 0) |
|`<<context-tiddler>>` |entries, actions, filters, visibility |Tiddler the user was looking at when the palette opened (focused `[data-tiddler-title]` ancestor, falling back to `$:/HistoryList`'s top entry). Empty when no context was captured. |
|`<arg>` |filter / visibility tiddler `expr` field |The sanitised user-supplied argument. Operand-form: `[<arg>]`. |
|`<<arg>>` |filter / visibility tiddler `chip` / `hint` / `help` fields |Plain-text version of the same argument. |

! Mount point

The widget is injected into `document.body` at boot via the startup module `widgets/cascade-palette-startup.js`. Mount-point ID: `rimir-cascade-palette-mount`. To inspect: `document.getElementById("rimir-cascade-palette-mount")`.

! Console diagnostics

The widget only logs on error paths (no boot noise):

* `[cascade-palette] startup mount complete — widget in document.body` — startup module ran successfully (one-time at boot)
* `[cascade-palette] action invocation failed: ...` — `invokeViaNavigator()` threw (most likely a filter or wikitext error in `ca-actions` / `ca-next-scope` / `ca-next-default-action`)
* `[cascade-palette] ca-visibility-filter error on ...` — a root-entry's visibility filter threw; entry stays visible defensively
* `[cascade-palette] ca-template-applies error on ...` — a template's filter threw; template is excluded
* `[cascade-palette] template render error ...` — the template body wikitext failed to parse; the drawer shows the error message in place of the template
* `[cascade-palette] stack depth N exceeds soft warning M — possible cascade loop?` — the user has drilled past the soft-depth-warning threshold
